 <H1>Primary Key Constraints</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>A set of fields is a key for a relation if :
</H2>
<UL>
1. No two distinct tuples can have same values in all key fields, and
<BR><BR>2. This is not true for any subset of the key.
<LI>Part 2 false? A superkey.
<LI>If there’s &#0621 key for a relation, one of the keys is chosen (by DBA) to be the primary key.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>E.g., sid is a key for Students.  (What about name?)  The set {sid, gpa} is a superkey.</H2>
</UL></P>
